            <h2>Introduction to the Inventory System</h2>
            <p>Welcome to our Inventory System! Our system is designed to efficiently manage and monitor your inventory, providing you with the tools you need to streamline your inventory processes.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="features-functionality">
            <h2>Features and Functionality</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Item In/Out:</strong> Easily add or reduce the quantity of items in your inventory.</li>
                <li><strong>Monitoring of the Items:</strong> Keep track of item quantities, maximum limits, last updates, and responsible users.</li>
                <li><strong>Creating/Sending/Printing of Reports:</strong> Generate, send, and print detailed reports for better analysis.</li>
                <li><strong>Items Need to Buy:</strong> Automatically record items that need to be replenished based on reduced quantities.</li>
                <li><strong>Export and Import of Data:</strong> Seamlessly transfer data in and out of the system for backup or integration purposes.</li>
                <li><strong>Local and Cloud Data Storage:</strong> Store your inventory data locally or in the cloud for accessibility and backup.</li>
                <li><strong>Change Logs:</strong> Keep a detailed history of all changes made to the inventory data for auditing purposes.</li>
                <li><strong>SMS Notification:</strong> Receive notifications via SMS when inventory quantities reach critical levels.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="technology-stack">
            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>MongoDB:</strong> MongoDB is a NoSQL database used for storing and managing the inventory data. Its flexible document model allows for easy scalability and efficient querying.</li>
                <li><strong>Express.js:</strong> Express.js is a minimalist web framework for Node.js that provides a robust set of features for building web applications. It handles routing, middleware, and HTTP requests, making it ideal for creating RESTful APIs to interact with the MongoDB database.</li>
                <li><strong>Handlebars:</strong> Handlebars is a templating engine used for generating dynamic HTML content on the server-side. It allows for the creation of reusable templates and partials, simplifying the process of building complex web pages.</li>
                <li><strong>Node.js:</strong> Node.js is a server-side JavaScript runtime environment that allows developers to build scalable and high-performance web applications. It provides an event-driven architecture and non-blocking I/O model, making it suitable for handling concurrent connections and real-time applications.</li>
                <li>For SMS notification, the system utilizes the <strong>Twilio API</strong>.</li>
                <li>To package the project into a desktop application, <strong>Electron.js</strong> is employed.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

